<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="easy-adj">easy <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'iːzi/    美 /'iːzi/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>容易的；不费力的；易懂的</strong></h4>
<p>反 hard, difficult </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an easy exam / job 
容易的考试/工作</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The park is <strong>within easy</strong> walking <strong>distance</strong> (= close enough to walk to).
公园离得很近，步行很快便可到达。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>舒适的；安逸的；安心的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 uneasy, hard </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He lives <strong>an easy life</strong> in the country. 
他在乡下过着舒适安逸的生活。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't feel easy about letting the kids go out alone.
让这些孩子单独出去我不放心。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>[只用于名词前] 易受攻击的；容易吃亏的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tourists are an <strong>easy target</strong> for thieves. 
游客容易成为小偷下手的目标。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>易相处的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is gentle and easy to approach. 
她很温柔，也容易相处。</p></div></div>